\f2\i Sogomsh
\f0\i0  was spoken throughout the Land. Whether it is truly as the First Arrivers say or not, both the 
\f2\i Sogomsh
\f0\i0  language and the Arqa language seem to have emerged from this area and then spread across the southern Saskan Lands.\
\

\f2\i Sogomsh
\f0\i0  is the main language used in Arq province, not the eponymous Arqa language. Residents of the town of Barqton pride themselves for being the hosts of the oldest 
\f2\i Sogomsh
\f0\i0  Language Academy and resist any attempts by others, particular those from the Runes of Bye, where the language is widely and vigorously used, to claim intellectual ownership over it. But despite those claims, most would agree that, as in so many other academic areas, the 
\f2\i best
\f0\i0  language schools for both Sogomsh and Arqa are probably in Byenung.
